  "purpose": "Contrastive (state, action, outcome) trace pack for the world-model baselines (Cluster D). Unlike the original 25-pair Path-A corpus, every action appears with BOTH a success and a failure outcome under different states, so a predictor must read the STATE to be right — it cannot win by ignoring the action context or by always voting the majority class. 'outcome' is the success label (1=passed, 0=failed) following agent.verified_world_model.OutcomePair. The train/val splits share task-families (in-distribution, retrievable); the shift split mixes (a) near-train queries the retrieval floor should answer correctly and (b) genuinely NOVEL task-families that are OOD by construction and MUST be abstained on, not guessed.",
  "honestBound": "Hand-authored demo data, not mined model traces. It is realistic (each action is contrastive: success when the state supplies the precondition, failure when it does not) but it is a fixture, not evidence. It exists so the retrieval-floor and self-consistency baselines can be exercised deterministically in CI; it does not prove generalization and nothing here lets canClaimAGI flip.",
  "positiveRate": 0.5,
